01:37:50,315 --> 01:37:52,996
The man's being transferred
to a new duty station, Eileen,

1465

01:37:53,036 --> 01:37:54,155
along with many others.

1466

01:37:54,196 --> 01:37:56,716
Now, don't ask me
the reasons for changes of duty.

1467

01:37:57,156 --> 01:37:58,636
There are thousands of them.

1468

01:37:58,716 --> 01:38:01,036
But Lloyd said
that most of the men on this particular list

1469

01:38:01,076 --> 01:38:02,637
are married to Japanese girls.

1470

01:38:02,676 --> 01:38:04,236
That can't be just
a coincidence, Father.

1471

01:38:04,316 --> 01:38:05,517
Why not?
It could easily be.

1472

01:38:05,596 --> 01:38:07,596
There have been
lots of marriages.

1473

01:38:07,677 --> 01:38:09,796
Frankly, with some
of these men,

1474

01:38:10,076 --> 01:38:12,717
I think they might
welcome the transfer.

1475

01:38:13,157 --> 01:38:14,437
Why is that, sir?

1476

01:38:14,996 --> 01:38:18,437
There have been unfortunate
aftermaths to many of these marriages.

1477

01:38:18,477 --> 01:38:20,397
Recriminations, regrets.

1478

01:38:22,118 --> 01:38:24,397
A boy gets married
impulsively, then feels caught,

1479

01:38:24,477 --> 01:38:26,677
doesn't know how to get out of
it, doesn't know what to do.

1480

01:38:26,758 --> 01:38:29,198
Change of duty
gives them both a chance to think it over.

1481

01:38:29,277 --> 01:38:30,397
To cool off.

1482

01:38:31,597 --> 01:38:33,558
Now, I don't mean to
imply that that's the reason

1483

01:38:33,638 --> 01:38:35,718
these men are being
transferred, but...

1484

01:38:36,078 --> 01:38:37,358
Well...

1485

01:38:38,918 --> 01:38:40,479
The whole thing's

1486

01:38:41,398 --> 01:38:42,718
a messy business.

1487

01:38:44,278 --> 01:38:47,759
General Webster, there is no regret in the
case of Kelly and Katsumi.

1488

01:38:48,799 --> 01:38:50,639
You can have
my word on that.

1489

01:38:51,039 --> 01:38:51,999
Lloyd,

1490

01:38:52,959 --> 01:38:54,959
three officers
came to me today

1491

01:38:55,039 --> 01:38:56,999
with identical requests
for their men.

1492

01:38:57,479 --> 01:38:59,199
It's not our policy
to interfere with decisions

1493

01:38:59,280 --> 01:39:01,439
made by immediate
commanding officers.

1494

01:39:01,519 --> 01:39:04,040
The basic structure
of the whole military service would collapse

1495

01:39:04,080 --> 01:39:05,919
if we started doing
things like that.

1496

01:39:07,399 --> 01:39:09,440
Your father would
understand that, even if you don't.

1497

01:39:10,959 --> 01:39:13,200
Are you going to
ask me to make an exception of Kelly

1498

01:39:13,240 --> 01:39:14,800
when I've refused
these other men?

1499

01:39:18,000 --> 01:39:20,241
I am going to ask you
to do that, sir.

1500

01:39:22,161 --> 01:39:24,840
You made an exception of me
when you brought me from Korea.

1501

01:39:27,761 --> 01:39:30,601
I'm afraid
it's a hopeless situation, Lloyd.

1502

01:39:35,841 --> 01:39:36,801
Well...

1503

01:39:39,081 --> 01:39:40,842
That's the end of Joe Kelly.

1504

01:39:42,361 --> 01:39:45,401
You told me yourself
that Kelly's past record was against him.

1505

01:39:45,482 --> 01:39:47,202
I couldn't even use that,
don't you see?

1506

01:39:47,282 --> 01:39:49,642
Why does this mean
so much to you, Lloyd?

1507

01:39:52,242 --> 01:39:55,802
Kelly's from my outfit, Mrs. Webster.
I was his best man.

1508

01:39:56,402 --> 01:39:59,043
And I'm planning to marry
a Japanese girl myself.

1509

01:40:03,683 --> 01:40:05,682
Come into the other room, Eileen.

1510

01:40:05,763 --> 01:40:07,803
This is something
for your father to handle.

1511

01:40:08,523 --> 01:40:12,083
No, Mrs. Webster, I don't think it's
anything for anybody to handle.

1512

01:40:18,323 --> 01:40:19,683
I'm sorry, Eileen.

1513

01:40:24,764 --> 01:40:25,964
Mrs. Webster.

1514

01:40:26,564 --> 01:40:28,004
Good afternoon, y'all.

1515

01:40:34,165 --> 01:40:37,845
I don't think I'll ever love anyone
again as much as I love Lloyd.

1516

01:40:39,164 --> 01:40:41,204
But I'll tell you something
that's rather ironic.

1517

01:40:42,844 --> 01:40:45,805
I once asked Lloyd
if he ever felt like grabbing me

1518

01:40:46,165 --> 01:40:48,445
and hauling me off
to a shack somewhere.

1519

01:40:50,325 --> 01:40:52,006
That's just what
he's done, isn't it?

1520

01:40:52,805 --> 01:40:54,165
Only it's with somebody else.

1521

01:40:55,365 --> 01:40:57,206
Don't go out, Eileen.

1522

01:40:57,245 --> 01:40:58,365
Stay and talk.

1523

01:40:58,446 --> 01:40:59,766
I'm sorry, Mother.

1524

01:40:59,846 --> 01:41:02,166
There's only one person
I'd like to talk to at the moment,

1525

01:41:02,646 --> 01:41:04,726
and oddly enough,
he's Japanese.

1526

01:41:09,366 --> 01:41:10,966
Ace, I've been
waiting for you.

1527

01:41:11,046 --> 01:41:12,406
Hey, Kelly, listen.

1528

01:41:12,847 --> 01:41:15,806
I just came from
General Webster's house

1529

01:41:15,887 --> 01:41:17,367
and there's a whole
big mess there.

1530

01:41:17,446 --> 01:41:18,646
-No good, huh?
- No.

1531

01:41:19,127 --> 01:41:21,526
He didn't...
He didn't go for it.

1532

01:41:22,367 --> 01:41:24,887
Matter of fact,
I think I even messed it up a little.

1533

01:41:26,527 --> 01:41:27,967
That figures.

1534

01:41:28,727 --> 01:41:30,247
Did you tell
Katsumi yet?

1535

01:41:30,327 --> 01:41:31,327
No.

1536

01:41:32,087 --> 01:41:33,727
I'm chickening out fast.

1537

01:41:34,607 --> 01:41:37,648
Besides, she's got her heart set on
something she planned for us tonight.

1538

01:41:38,088 --> 01:41:39,728
Wants us both to take
the train to Osaka

1539

01:41:39,767 --> 01:41:41,848
and meet the girls
at the puppet show.

1540

01:41:43,448 --> 01:41:44,689
Why Spoil it?

1541

01:41:47,168 --> 01:41:49,408
Maybe I'll tell
her late tonight when we're alone.

1542

01:41:52,369 --> 01:41:55,329
Kelly, don't give up on it.
I think there's gonna be a way out of it.

1543

01:41:55,408 --> 01:41:56,368
- There's got to be.
- You think so?

1544

01:41:56,409 --> 01:41:57,728
- Yes, I do.
-I don't.

1545

01:42:00,089 --> 01:42:01,369
- I'll see you, Ace.
- Hi, hon.

1546

01:42:01,409 --> 01:42:02,369
Kelly-san.

1547

01:42:03,890 --> 01:42:06,129
Hey, tell Katsumi
we'll be there with bells.

1548

01:42:07,689 --> 01:42:09,210
Were you able to help?

1549

01:42:12,689 --> 01:42:14,250
No. I wasn't.

1550

01:42:14,329 --> 01:42:15,770
How terrible.

1551

01:42:19,730 --> 01:42:21,050
I know this is hard, honey.

1552

01:42:21,090 --> 01:42:23,290
It's hard,
but it's not gonna last long.

1553

01:42:23,330 --> 01:42:26,931
I mean, the Army's got to change that
law next year or the next one.

1554

01:42:27,891 --> 01:42:30,771
I mean, it just has to be.
I'm sure of it.

1555

01:42:32,691 --> 01:42:34,651
And, as a matter of fact,

1556

01:42:34,691 --> 01:42:37,331
I'm so sure of it
that I went downtown today

1557

01:42:37,370 --> 01:42:39,931
and I signed
some papers here

1558

01:42:39,971 --> 01:42:42,211
that mean that you and I
are gonna get married.

1559

01:42:45,172 --> 01:42:46,291
What's the matter?

1560

01:42:46,331 --> 01:42:47,931
We never spoke of marriage.

1561

01:42:48,812 --> 01:42:50,772
I know we didn't, darling.

1562

01:42:51,651 --> 01:42:55,852
I know we didn't.
I been going round and round with that

1563

01:42:55,932 --> 01:42:57,852
every day for a long time.

1564

01:42:58,772 --> 01:43:01,893
And I didn't feel I could
speak about it until now.

1565

01:43:03,292 --> 01:43:04,572
Now I can.

1566

01:43:06,413 --> 01:43:09,732
Now, of course,
I won't be able to take you back to America,

1567

01:43:09,813 --> 01:43:12,413
but they're bound to change
that ridiculous law soon.

1568

01:43:13,813 --> 01:43:16,253
And until then,
I'm gonna stay here with you.

1569

01:43:18,494 --> 01:43:21,453
I'm not stuck in the Air Force.
I can resign.

1570

01:43:21,533 --> 01:43:24,573
Of course,
I'm not trained to do anything else,

1571

01:43:25,373 --> 01:43:26,454
but I'd find something.

1572

01:43:27,934 --> 01:43:29,974
We never spoke of marriage.

1573

01:43:31,454 --> 01:43:34,814
I know we didn't, darling,
but we're speaking of it now.

1574

01:43:42,134 --> 01:43:44,854
Do you remember
the first night we talked?

1575

01:43:45,534 --> 01:43:49,254
I said there would
be danger of weakness when it is over.

1576

01:43:52,415 --> 01:43:54,735
Over?
What are you talking about?

1577

01:43:58,095 --> 01:44:01,256
I am tempted.
With you, I could become a woman.

1578

01:44:02,175 --> 01:44:05,496
And a mother.
And I could love you.

1579

01:44:07,615 --> 01:44:08,976
That's right.

1580

01:44:09,535 --> 01:44:12,056
Do you think I haven't
thought about it?

1581

01:44:12,536 --> 01:44:15,456
Do you think
I want to become a lonely old woman

1582

01:44:15,496 --> 01:44:18,977
who teaches dancing,
now that I have known you?

1583

01:44:21,297 --> 01:44:22,897
But it is no good.

1584

01:44:23,976 --> 01:44:25,257
You must know it, too.

1585

01:44:25,657 --> 01:44:28,937
No, no. I don't know
anything of the kind.

1586

01:44:30,537 --> 01:44:33,097
The way you talk about
leaving the Air Force,

1587

01:44:34,177 --> 01:44:36,658
finding some pitiful
way of earning living

1588

01:44:36,737 --> 01:44:39,177
just to be here with
your Japanese wife.

1589

01:44:39,497 --> 01:44:41,418
Now, wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1590

01:44:44,698 --> 01:44:47,657
I think we're too far
in this thing to be talking like that.

1591

01:44:49,498 --> 01:44:52,098
Matsubayashi has been
kind to me, Lloyd.

1592

01:44:53,578 --> 01:44:55,459
I am obligated to them.

1593

01:44:55,898 --> 01:44:59,458
No, you ain't.
You... No, no. You obligated to me.

1594

01:45:00,939 --> 01:45:02,498
They are my life.

1595

01:45:03,099 --> 01:45:05,859
I will bring shame
to them, disgrace.

1596

01:45:06,819 --> 01:45:08,899
Lloyd, you know
what I mean?

1597

01:45:08,979 --> 01:45:12,419
Yeah, I think
I'm beginning to know what you mean.

1598

01:45:12,460 --> 01:45:16,180
I think you mean you simply don't love me
enough to go on through with it.

1599

01:45:16,260 --> 01:45:18,379
That's what you mean,
don't you?

1600

01:45:18,460 --> 01:45:20,780
Why don't you
just come on out and say it?

1601

01:45:20,859 --> 01:45:22,660
It is not what I mean.

1602

01:45:27,380 --> 01:45:29,700
I'm leaving for Tokyo
in six days.

1603

01:45:30,620 --> 01:45:32,901
Matsubayashi are sending me.

1604

01:45:32,980 --> 01:45:34,620
You What?

1605

01:45:36,701 --> 01:45:40,701
With another troupe.
They have found out about us.

1606

01:45:41,861 --> 01:45:45,741
Any other girl, they would have
dismissed, but because they like me,

1607

01:45:45,821 --> 01:45:49,981
because they feel I am important
to them, they are being lenient.

1608

01:45:51,301 --> 01:45:53,661
Well, I'm not gonna be
lenient with you.

1609

01:45:54,501 --> 01:45:55,821
I want you to
tell me right now

1610

01:45:55,902 --> 01:45:58,662
why Matsubayashi
means more to you than I do?

1611

01:46:01,542 --> 01:46:04,382
Lloyd, there is something
about myself

1612

01:46:04,422 --> 01:46:05,862
I have not told you.

1613

01:46:07,222 --> 01:46:09,462
I have no right
to marry anyone.

1614

01:46:10,502 --> 01:46:12,422
My father was very poor.

1615

01:46:13,623 --> 01:46:16,103
To save his other children,

1616

01:46:16,183 --> 01:46:18,623
he was forced to sell
one of his daughters.

1617

01:46:20,263 --> 01:46:23,303
The man from the houses
of Yoshiwara came to him.

1618

01:46:24,863 --> 01:46:26,863
Because I was the oldest,

1619

01:46:28,103 --> 01:46:30,344
he agreed I should
go with them.

1620

01:46:32,223 --> 01:46:34,344
Your father sold you?

1621

01:46:35,463 --> 01:46:39,224
Yes, but I was saved
from starting this life

1622

01:46:39,784 --> 01:46:41,904
by my best friend,
Fumiko-san.

1623

01:46:44,424 --> 01:46:46,825
Her father paid
money to free me

1624

01:46:48,345 --> 01:46:50,744
and she brought me
to Matsubayashi.

1625

01:46:54,185 --> 01:46:56,905
There, I not only
earn my living,

1626

01:46:58,224 --> 01:47:00,745
I brought honor
back to my family.

1627

01:47:03,305 --> 01:47:05,665
Matsubayashi has
been kind to me.

1628

01:47:06,465 --> 01:47:08,186
They have trusted me.

1629

01:47:09,706 --> 01:47:11,306
I cannot leave them.

1630

01:47:12,306 --> 01:47:14,186
I cannot marry anyone.

1631

01:47:18,146 --> 01:47:20,186
Don't you understand?

1632

01:47:26,666 --> 01:47:27,866
I don't know.

1633

01:47:29,786 --> 01:47:30,947
I don't know
what to think.

1634

01:47:34,227 --> 01:47:35,267
I'll kill you!

1635

01:47:35,307 --> 01:47:36,707
You ever do
anything like this,

1636

01:47:36,747 --> 01:47:38,067
and I'll kill you,
you understand?

1637

01:47:38,147 --> 01:47:40,147
Get that straight, now!
I'll kill you!

1638

01:47:40,227 --> 01:47:42,307
Wait a minute. Listen.
Just take it easy, now.

1639

01:47:42,348 --> 01:47:43,707
Ace, look at this.

1640
01:47:46,348 --> 01:47:48,027
-It fell out of her bag.
- What is it?

1641

01:47:48,108 --> 01:47:49,868
She was gonna
have it done, too.

1642

01:47:49,908 --> 01:47:52,348
Tomorrow,
by that quack doctor down by the docks.

1643

01:47:52,428 --> 01:47:54,548
- What?
-For 8 bucks, she slashes her eyelids

1644

01:47:54,628 --> 01:47:56,668
and sews them
back up again.

1645

01:47:56,748 --> 01:47:58,788
Lots of these stupid little jerks
have it done.

1646

01:47:58,829 --> 01:48:00,349
She was gonna surprise me.

1647

01:48:01,029 --> 01:48:01,989
Well...

1648

01:48:02,028 --> 01:48:03,148
Then...

1649

01:48:03,229 --> 01:48:06,948
Then I have good eyes.
I fool everybody.

1650

01:48:07,309 --> 01:48:10,069
I look American, like Joe.

1651

01:48:11,149 --> 01:48:16,069
Hana-ogi, will you tell
that stupid dame I love her the way she is?

1652

01:48:16,469 --> 01:48:17,989
I don't want her changed.

1653

01:48:18,030 --> 01:48:19,790
Will you tell her
I love her mouth

1654

01:48:19,829 --> 01:48:22,950
and her nose
and her ears and her eyes

1655

01:48:22,989 --> 01:48:24,669
just the way they are?

1656

01:48:24,750 --> 01:48:27,870
Tell her if she ever does
anything like that, I'll...

1657

01:48:28,590 --> 01:48:29,830
Wait a minute.
Calm down, Kelly.

1658

01:48:29,870 --> 01:48:32,190
I want him
be proud of me.

1659

01:48:32,270 --> 01:48:33,390
Listen, listen. Listen.

1660

01:48:33,630 --> 01:48:35,190
I am sorry.

1661

01:48:35,270 --> 01:48:38,191
Listen, if you want him
to be proud of you, you got to quit this stuff.

1662

01:48:38,270 --> 01:48:39,630
‘Cause you want to be
a good wife, don't you?

1663

01:48:39,671 --> 01:48:41,711
You're making him
very unhappy when you're doing that.

1664

01:48:41,790 --> 01:48:43,951
Now, tell him you're sorry
and you're not going to do it anymore.

1665

01:48:43,990 --> 01:48:45,230
Tell him that.

1666

01:48:45,311 --> 01:48:46,271
Joe...

1667

01:48:48,431 --> 01:48:50,191
I so sorry.

1668

01:48:52,631 --> 01:48:55,472
Okay. Now, we're gonna
forget about that, all right?

1669

01:48:56,071 --> 01:48:57,631
Now, listen.
I came over here tonight,

1670

01:48:57,711 --> 01:48:59,272
I thought we were gonna
have a fish fry.

1671

01:48:59,312 --> 01:49:01,431
We were gonna have some fun right
here, and dancing and yelling,

1672

01:49:01,512 --> 01:49:02,752
and what do I find?

1673

01:49:02,832 --> 01:49:04,271
What's gonna happen to us?

1674

01:49:04,352 --> 01:49:05,352
Puppet show.

1675

01:49:05,391 --> 01:49:07,232
-Yeah, we had a surprise...
- You like?

1676

01:49:07,312 --> 01:49:08,952
Sure, I do.
Been looking forward to it.

1677

01:49:09,472 --> 01:49:11,792
I know everybody tonight.

1678

01:49:11,872 --> 01:49:13,033
Yeah.

1679

01:49:15,952 --> 01:49:16,912
And

1680

01:49:17,312 --> 01:49:18,672
we will be late.

1681

01:49:26,433 --> 01:49:27,433
Look.

1682

01:49:28,113 --> 01:49:32,593
The lover is leaving the city,
walk to the wood.

1683

01:50:08,675 --> 01:50:12,195
Lloyd, don't think
of anything now.

1684

01:50:13,356 --> 01:50:14,836
Watch the play.

1685

01:50:15,635 --> 01:50:17,356
It's a tender story.

1686

01:50:25,516 --> 01:50:29,116
When gong sound,
it is done.

1687

01:50:29,436 --> 01:50:34,156
And then she will
bind her body.

1688

01:50:35,677 --> 01:50:37,037
Bind her body?

1689

01:50:37,077 --> 01:50:40,237
So that she will not fall
in an ugly position

1690

01:50:40,276 --> 01:50:42,357
of dishonor when she dies.

1691

01:50:42,757 --> 01:50:43,797
- When she dies?
- Mmm.

1692

01:50:43,877 --> 01:50:45,157
Yes, shinju.

1693

01:51:02,358 --> 01:51:04,438
It is custom for lovers

1694

01:51:04,518 --> 01:51:07,718
to die together
when they can no longer face life.

1695

01:51:18,159 --> 01:51:20,199
It is so beautiful.

1696

01:51:21,079 --> 01:51:23,799
Beautiful?
They're gonna die, aren't they?

1697

01:51:24,479 --> 01:51:28,680
They will live
in another world on a beautiful lake

1698

01:51:29,239 --> 01:51:31,479
floating always together

1699

01:51:32,240 --> 01:51:33,880
like water lily.

1700

01:51:36,960 --> 01:51:38,040
Sure.

1701

01:52:56,804 --> 01:52:59,725
Kelly-san! Kelly-san!
Kelly-san!

1702

01:53:09,764 --> 01:53:11,965
Something about soldiers
going through the house.

1703

01:53:17,605 --> 01:53:18,725
That's the MPs, boy.

1704

01:53:18,806 --> 01:53:20,485
-What happened? What's wrong?
- Come here, come here.

1705

01:53:20,566 --> 01:53:22,086
- What happened?
- Get in the car.

1706

01:53:24,766 --> 01:53:25,965
Go to Matsubayashi.

1707

01:53:26,046 --> 01:53:27,806
- Please, please tell me. I will not leave.
- I will, I will.

1708

01:53:27,846 --> 01:53:29,245
Now, get in the car.
I'll tell you later.

1709

01:53:29,326 --> 01:53:30,766
Matsubayashi.

1710

01:53:33,406 --> 01:53:34,606
Hey, Ed, look.

1711

01:53:50,207 --> 01:53:51,287
Look at that.

1712

01:53:54,367 --> 01:53:55,808
You're Major Gruver,
aren't you?

1713

01:53:56,567 --> 01:53:57,567
That's right.

1714

01:53:57,647 --> 01:53:59,088
Sorry, Major, you'll have
to come with us.

1715

01:53:59,167 --> 01:54:00,287
General Webster's orders.

1716

01:54:00,448 --> 01:54:02,528
So, what right do
you have to board up this man's house?

1717

01:54:02,567 --> 01:54:04,008
He won't be needing
it anymore, Major.

1718

01:54:04,087 --> 01:54:05,128
He's shipping out Thursday.

1719

01:54:05,248 --> 01:54:06,208
Joe?

1720

01:54:07,128 --> 01:54:08,448
Come on, Major.

1721

01:54:10,528 --> 01:54:12,048
You'll hear from me, Kelly.

1722

01:54:25,929 --> 01:54:27,449
Come on, kid.

1723

01:54:27,489 --> 01:54:31,090
We'll get in through the garden.
I got something to tell you.

1724

01:54:53,370 --> 01:54:54,850
You were seen
in public with her tonight,

1725

01:54:54,891 --> 01:54:56,931
violating the orders
of the area.

1726

01:54:56,971 --> 01:54:59,090
This has given
me the right to put you under arrest.

1727

01:55:00,411 --> 01:55:02,651
And, for your own sake,
I think I'd better do it.

1728

01:55:03,771 --> 01:55:04,731
Well,

1729

01:55:05,251 --> 01:55:06,651
you have anything to say?

1730

01:55:09,052 --> 01:55:12,052
Well, just as soon I'm out of this,
I'm going to be married,

1731

01:55:12,131 --> 01:55:13,491
and have a house of my own.

1732

01:55:15,892 --> 01:55:17,372
I'm afraid not.

1733

01:55:17,812 --> 01:55:20,012
I'm sorry, Lloyd,
but it's all settled.

1734

01:55:20,092 --> 01:55:23,372
The supervisor of the Matsubayashi
came to see me tonight.

1735

01:55:23,852 --> 01:55:26,332
The girl goes
to Tokyo, and you fly to Randolph Field,

1736

01:55:26,852 --> 01:55:27,892
day after tomorrow.

1737

01:55:28,772 --> 01:55:30,252
Here are your orders.

1738

01:55:31,573 --> 01:55:33,613
Until that time,
you're under house arrest.

1739

01:55:35,452 --> 01:55:38,733
You're not to leave
your quarters until further notice.

1740

01:55:43,973 --> 01:55:47,013
I'm doing this because I feel you're not
responsible at the moment, Lloyd.

1741

01:55:47,093 --> 01:55:49,413
After all, I've known
your father for years.

1742

01:55:55,374 --> 01:55:56,934
Well, that's all.

1743

01:56:31,176 --> 01:56:32,215
Mike...

1744

01:56:33,295 --> 01:56:34,376
Did you see her?

1745

01:56:34,456 --> 01:56:35,776
No, Ace. I couldn't even get
near the place.

1746

01:56:35,816 --> 01:56:36,816
They've really clamped down.

1747

01:56:36,896 --> 01:56:39,016
I went to the stage
door and I couldn't even see Fumiko-san.

1748

01:56:39,096 --> 01:56:41,657
Well, listen, I've got to see her.
I'm being shipped out of here tomorrow.

1749

01:56:42,016 --> 01:56:43,376
Major Gruver?

1750

01:56:43,456 --> 01:56:44,537
What is it?

1751

01:56:44,616 --> 01:56:45,737
Would you do
something for us?

1752

01:56:45,776 --> 01:56:46,977
What do you want?

1753
01:56:47,736 --> 01:56:49,257
Airman Kelly's disappeared.

1754

01:56:49,337 --> 01:56:52,217
No, that's impossible.
I was with him just last night.

1755

01:56:52,297 --> 01:56:53,297
We know.

1756

01:56:53,377 --> 01:56:54,777
He was scheduled to fly out
in a couple days.

1757

01:56:54,857 --> 01:56:58,257
But a special plane came through, and
Colonel Crawford told us to get him on it.

1758

01:56:58,337 --> 01:57:00,657
I took him to
the airport at 12:50.

1759

01:57:00,737 --> 01:57:03,458
When the plane took off,
Kelly wasn't on it.

1760

01:57:03,497 --> 01:57:04,778
Figured you might
know where he is.

1761

01:57:04,818 --> 01:57:08,058
How should I know where he is?
His house has been boarded up, hasn't it?

1762

01:57:08,137 --> 01:57:10,858
We know.
Neighbors won't talk to us.

1763

01:57:10,938 --> 01:57:12,538
We figure maybe
they're hiding him.

1764

01:57:13,098 --> 01:57:15,538
They'll talk with you, Major.
Would you help us?

1765

01:57:16,418 --> 01:57:19,018
Well, would you give
me one good reason why I should?

1766

01:57:21,019 --> 01:57:22,818
We figured we'd
give him a break.

1767

01:57:22,858 --> 01:57:24,458
We haven't reported
him as yet.

1768

01:57:24,498 --> 01:57:26,499
We could get him
on another plane.

1769

01:57:26,538 --> 01:57:28,499
We might not have
to turn him in for desertion.

1770

01:57:30,579 --> 01:57:32,259
- Desertion?
-Yes, sir.

1771

01:57:35,979 --> 01:57:37,099
Well...

1772

01:57:38,739 --> 01:57:40,299
I'll go with
you in a minute.

1773

01:57:40,819 --> 01:57:41,939
Major?

1774

01:57:42,380 --> 01:57:44,779
The neighbors won't
talk if they see an MP.

1775

01:57:44,820 --> 01:57:45,900
I'll go with him.

1776

01:57:45,980 --> 01:57:47,460
Thank you, sir.

1777

01:58:45,583 --> 01:58:46,783
Kelly?

1778

01:58:49,983 --> 01:58:51,503
Kelly, Gruver out here.

1779

01:58:53,903 --> 01:58:55,183
I think he's in there.

1780

01:58:57,343 --> 01:58:58,384
Kelly?

1781

01:59:00,463 --> 01:59:01,983
I'm going on in.

1782

01:59:15,464 --> 01:59:16,504
Kelly?

1783

01:59:23,625 --> 01:59:24,625
Kelly?

1784

01:59:31,185 --> 01:59:33,425
Kelly, you in there?

1785

01:59:56,547 --> 01:59:57,987
Oh, my God.

1786

02:00:01,747 --> 02:00:02,707
Oh, my...

1787

02:00:11,308 --> 02:00:12,268
Oh...

1788

02:00:14,188 --> 02:00:15,148
Oh.

1789

02:00:23,028 --> 02:00:24,109
Oh.

1790

02:00:26,149 --> 02:00:27,188
Oh.

1791

02:00:30,669 --> 02:00:32,628
I'll call the police, Ace.

1792

02:00:49,909 --> 02:00:51,070
Oh, God.

1793

02:02:24,475 --> 02:02:27,195
Go home! Go home!

1794

02:02:28,155 --> 02:02:32,475
Go home! Go home! Go home!

1795

02:02:33,155 --> 02:02:36,635
Ace, there's no police around.
We'd better get out of here.

1796

02:02:38,236 --> 02:02:39,316
Hey, look.

1797

02:02:47,076 --> 02:02:48,476
Doesn't look too good, boy.

1798

02:02:51,676 --> 02:02:54,557
Go home! Go home!

1799

02:02:55,316 --> 02:02:56,676
Come on, take it easy.

1800

02:03:28,398 --> 02:03:30,038
We're getting help, Ace.

1801

02:03:43,239 --> 02:03:45,199
- You okay, boy?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

1802

02:03:45,279 --> 02:03:46,479
You all right?

1803

02:03:46,559 --> 02:03:47,599
Yeah.

1804

02:03:48,199 --> 02:03:49,519
Listen, I'm going to...

1805

02:03:50,520 --> 02:03:52,599
I want you to take care of everything.
Will you?

1806

02:03:52,639 --> 02:03:54,239
- Oh, yeah, I'll get it...
- Okay.

1807

02:03:55,239 --> 02:03:56,360
I'll see you later.

1808

02:04:42,402 --> 02:04:43,482
Hey, where's Hana-ogi?

1809

02:04:43,522 --> 02:04:44,722
Hana-ogi's not here.

1810

02:04:44,802 --> 02:04:46,362
Oh, I know she's here.

1811

02:04:46,402 --> 02:04:47,882
She is on her way Tokyo.

1812

02:04:47,963 --> 02:04:50,242
No, she wasn't... She wasn't
supposed to go to Tokyo till next week.

1813

02:04:50,283 --> 02:04:51,442
She went today.

1814

02:04:51,523 --> 02:04:52,923
I don't believe you.

1815

02:04:52,962 --> 02:04:55,043
- Mr. Gruver...
- I don't believe you.

1816

02:04:55,203 --> 02:04:56,163
I don't care...

1817

02:05:41,326 --> 02:05:42,605
Hana-ogi?

1818

02:05:52,806 --> 02:05:55,726
Hana-ogi. Hana-ogi.

1819

02:05:56,366 --> 02:05:57,606
Hana-ogi.

1820

02:06:07,607 --> 02:06:08,646
Hana-ogi?

1821

02:06:15,727 --> 02:06:17,007
Gruver-san!

1822

02:06:17,087 --> 02:06:19,207
-Hey, where's Hana-ogi?
- She's gone.

1823

02:06:19,247 --> 02:06:20,688
- Where's her room?
-She's gone.

1824

02:06:20,767 --> 02:06:22,527
Listen, where's her room?

1825

02:06:23,408 --> 02:06:24,687
Come here.

1826

02:06:28,248 --> 02:06:30,288
Hana-ogi really gone, Major.

1827

02:06:30,727 --> 02:06:32,448
I don't believe you.

1828

02:06:33,168 --> 02:06:34,528
Hana-ogi.

1829

02:06:40,408 --> 02:06:42,089
I give you my word.

1830

02:06:42,729 --> 02:06:44,569
You go now, too, Major.

1831

02:06:45,369 --> 02:06:46,648
It's over.

1832

02:06:47,769 --> 02:06:49,928
Listen, leave me
alone a minute, will you?

1833

02:07:05,770 --> 02:07:08,970
The hoodlums who attacked
you weren't all your Japanese neighbors.

1834

02:07:09,210 --> 02:07:11,210
For the most part, they were
professional troublemakers

1835

02:07:11,250 --> 02:07:14,570
sent to your street
to create an incident specifically with you.

1836

02:07:15,330 --> 02:07:17,171
Now, if you're important
to those who hate us,

1837

02:07:18,090 --> 02:07:20,530
don't you see how
important you are to us?

1838

02:07:23,371 --> 02:07:25,291
Do you understand
any of this, Lloyd?

1839
02:07:28,331 --> 02:07:30,011
I know how you feel.

1840

02:07:30,331 --> 02:07:31,531
It was...

1841

02:07:32,292 --> 02:07:34,971
It was dreadful about
your friend Kelly and...

1842

02:07:36,091 --> 02:07:37,332
And his wife.

1843

02:07:39,731 --> 02:07:41,452
Must be hard to take.

1844

02:07:43,971 --> 02:07:45,012
And I...

1845

02:07:45,092 --> 02:07:49,212
I hate to tell you
something else, because it's

1846

02:07:50,092 --> 02:07:52,012
almost too grotesque.

1847

02:07:55,212 --> 02:07:57,373
Almost unforgivable in
your eyes, I imagine.

1848

02:07:58,252 --> 02:07:59,933
I got word today that...

1849

02:08:01,532 --> 02:08:04,013
There's a law being passed
in a month or two

1850

02:08:04,933 --> 02:08:07,333
that will make it possible
for men like Kelly

1851

02:08:08,373 --> 02:08:12,054
to take their
Japanese brides back to the States.

1852

02:08:16,454 --> 02:08:17,934
That can't be true, General.

1853

02:08:18,454 --> 02:08:20,934
Well, it happens
to be true, Lloyd.

1854

02:08:26,254 --> 02:08:27,454
Listen.

1855

02:08:28,294 --> 02:08:30,734
How do you get
the guts to come here and tell me that?

1856

02:08:31,655 --> 02:08:34,214
It takes time to get
laws passed, Lloyd.

1857

02:08:34,255 --> 02:08:38,255
And a lot of people have died
in this world needlessly, waiting for them.

1858

02:08:39,415 --> 02:08:40,415
Well, it's...

1859

02:08:40,495 --> 02:08:43,055
It's harder to take
when it hits you personally.

1860

02:08:45,975 --> 02:08:47,055
Lloyd...

1861

02:08:48,175 --> 02:08:50,255
You're lost. You're confused.

1862

02:08:52,175 --> 02:08:55,455
Don't you think it's time you got back
to the main stream of your life?

1863

02:08:56,056 --> 02:08:57,136
Back to your roots?

1864

02:08:57,176 --> 02:08:59,056
What you were born for,
and raised for?

1865

02:09:00,495 --> 02:09:02,376
You'll feel better
about everything when you get back home,

1866

02:09:02,416 --> 02:09:04,296
back to your work.

1867

02:09:07,457 --> 02:09:09,216
Appreciate you
coming over, General.

1868

02:09:49,859 --> 02:09:51,979
Take me to the airport, Mike.

1869

02:09:57,619 --> 02:09:59,339
That must be him.

1870

02:09:59,819 --> 02:10:01,299
Would you hold it,
so we can get a picture, General?

1871

02:10:01,380 --> 02:10:03,820
- Where would you like me? Right here?
-What about there? Yeah.

1872

02:10:05,819 --> 02:10:06,899
Smile, please.

1873

02:10:13,220 --> 02:10:15,020
Hey, Bill, isn't
that Ace Gruver?

1874

02:10:15,940 --> 02:10:16,980
Looks like him.

1875

02:10:19,700 --> 02:10:20,740
Sir?

1876

02:10:21,941 --> 02:10:24,421
Excuse me, aren't
you Major Gruver? Ace Gruver?

1877

02:10:24,500 --> 02:10:25,580
Yes, that's right.

1878

02:10:25,621 --> 02:10:26,900
Well, we're
from Stars and Stripes.

1879

02:10:26,981 --> 02:10:28,341
What are you doing
in Tokyo?

1880

02:10:28,941 --> 02:10:31,420
Well, I'm just passing
through, boys.

1881

02:10:31,501 --> 02:10:32,940
Just seeing the sights, huh?

1882

02:10:32,981 --> 02:10:36,341
That's right. Listen, I'm in a hurry.
Do you mind if I excuse myself?

1883

02:10:36,381 --> 02:10:38,101
- You're excused.
-Sorry.

1884

02:12:50,908 --> 02:12:51,908
Lloyd-san.

1885

02:13:13,350 --> 02:13:14,909
Hello, Hana-ogi.

1886

02:13:18,030 --> 02:13:20,510
I'm going back to
America on Friday.

1887

02:13:21,870 --> 02:13:23,710
And I probably won't

1888

02:13:24,870 --> 02:13:26,750
get back in Japan again.

1889

02:13:29,790 --> 02:13:32,070
And before I go,
there was just...

1890

02:13:33,870 --> 02:13:35,871
Just one thing
I wanted to know.

1891

02:13:38,751 --> 02:13:41,311
You remember one
time you said to me...

1892

02:13:43,751 --> 02:13:45,671
That you could love me

1893

02:13:47,551 --> 02:13:49,631
and be a wife and a mother?

1894

02:13:51,232 --> 02:13:52,511
I remember.

1895

02:13:55,352 --> 02:13:58,432
You said that since
you'd known me, you'd been afraid

1896

02:13:59,712 --> 02:14:01,952
of being
a lonely old woman, teaching dancing.

1897

02:14:02,752 --> 02:14:04,192
Remember that?

1898

02:14:05,633 --> 02:14:06,952
I remember.

1899

02:14:08,672 --> 02:14:11,633
Did you mean that
when you said it, Hana-ogi?

1900

02:14:13,113 --> 02:14:14,432
I meant it.

1901

02:14:15,313 --> 02:14:17,113
It is already happening.

1902

02:14:17,153 --> 02:14:20,193
Love has gone out
of my work, out of me.

1903

02:14:21,833 --> 02:14:24,193
Oh, Lloyd, please go now.

1904

02:14:25,073 --> 02:14:27,554
This will only
bring pain and trouble.

1905

02:14:29,953 --> 02:14:31,154
Hana-ogi,

1906

02:14:32,314 --> 02:14:34,394
you and I are going
to have more trouble

1907

02:14:34,434 --> 02:14:36,354
than we ever
thought of having in our whole lives

1908

02:14:36,394 --> 02:14:39,234
unless you're
absolutely honest with yourself.

1909

02:14:41,954 --> 02:14:45,314
Please, Lloyd, can't we
talk about this later?

1910

02:14:47,875 --> 02:14:49,795
There isn't
going to be any later.

1911

02:14:49,875 --> 02:14:51,754
There's only going
to be right now.

1912

02:14:52,755 --> 02:14:53,715
Oh, uh,

1913

02:14:53,955 --> 02:14:54,915
excuse me, Mother.

1914

02:14:55,995 --> 02:14:56,955
Excuse me.

1915

02:15:00,435 --> 02:15:02,035
I must return this robe.

1916

02:15:02,115 --> 02:15:03,435
Listen to me.

1917

02:15:03,516 --> 02:15:07,235
I want to know.
Do you love me, or don't you?

1918

02:15:09,236 --> 02:15:11,075
Because if you don't,

1919

02:15:11,156 --> 02:15:13,675
then I'm going to
have to find a way to live with it.

1920

02:15:14,716 --> 02:15:16,676
- And if you do, then...
- Please, Lloyd.

1921

02:15:18,916 --> 02:15:21,116
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute.

1922

02:15:24,477 --> 02:15:27,717
Now, I don't want you
to tell me anything more,

1923

02:15:27,757 --> 02:15:31,277
or anything less than
you feel in the very deepest part of you.

1924

02:15:32,397 --> 02:15:33,957
Because what you
answer to me now

1925

02:15:33,997 --> 02:15:36,597
is going to affect us
for the rest of our lives.

1926

02:15:39,438 --> 02:15:41,997
Do you love me, Hana-ogi,
or don't you love me?

1927

02:15:45,998 --> 02:15:48,198
I'm so frightened
and confused.

1928

02:15:48,838 --> 02:15:50,318
I cannot think.

1929

02:15:50,598 --> 02:15:52,518
I cannot even
understand your thinking.

1930

02:15:52,598 --> 02:15:54,238
I'm not thinking!
I'm not thinking...

1931

02:15:54,278 --> 02:15:57,438
For the first time in my life,
I'm not thinking, and I don't care.

1932

02:15:58,919 --> 02:16:00,918
But, Lloyd, we must
do the right thing.

1933

02:16:00,998 --> 02:16:03,559
Oh, what are you talking
about, the right thing?

1934

02:16:03,638 --> 02:16:05,319
We've been wasting
two good lives

1935

02:16:05,398 --> 02:16:06,478
trying to do
the right thing.

1936

02:16:06,559 --> 02:16:07,879
The right thing
for Matsubayashi,

1937

02:16:07,959 --> 02:16:10,439
the right thing
for my father,

1938

02:16:10,479 --> 02:16:11,639
the right thing
for the military,

1939

02:16:11,719 --> 02:16:14,439
the right thing for
Japanese tradition.

1940

02:16:14,519 --> 02:16:16,839
The right thing for
the great white race.

1941

02:16:17,639 --> 02:16:19,480
But we have duties
and obligations.

1942

02:16:19,559 --> 02:16:21,240
That's right, we do.

1943

02:16:21,719 --> 02:16:23,040
We have duties
and obligations.

1944

02:16:23,079 --> 02:16:26,120
And the first obligation we have
is to love each other.

1945

02:16:26,200 --> 02:16:29,880
To become man and wife,
and raise some clean, sweet children.

1946

02:16:29,960 --> 02:16:32,080
And give them
the very best that we know how.

1947

02:16:32,960 --> 02:16:35,080
And if we don't
meet that obligation,

1948

02:16:35,121 --> 02:16:37,161
we ain't going to be
any good to anybody.

1949

02:16:38,121 --> 02:16:41,641
We live in different worlds,
come from different races.

1950

02:16:42,081 --> 02:16:43,201
Oh.

1951

02:16:45,160 --> 02:16:47,760
Honey, I want you
to be my wife.

1952

02:16:49,841 --> 02:16:53,161
But what would happen to our children?
What would they be?

1953

02:16:53,721 --> 02:16:54,882
What would they be?

1954

02:16:55,402 --> 02:16:57,561
They'd be half Japanese,
half American.

1955

02:16:57,641 --> 02:17:00,042
They'd be half
yellow and half white.

1956

02:17:00,561 --> 02:17:03,082
They'd be half you,
they'd be half me.

1957

02:17:03,401 --> 02:17:05,602
That's all they're going to be.

1958

02:17:18,242 --> 02:17:20,842
Hana-ogi, I want you
to come with me now.

1959

02:17:22,683 --> 02:17:25,803
I want you to come with me now,
down to the American Consulate,

1960

02:17:27,243 --> 02:17:28,683
here in Tokyo.

1961

02:17:29,083 --> 02:17:32,444
We're gonna filling out those papers,
'cause we've only got a few days

1962

02:17:32,523 --> 02:17:35,083
to get this whole thing done,
and get it out of the way.

1963

02:17:44,004 --> 02:17:45,084
Will you come?

1964

02:17:55,845 --> 02:17:57,805
I'm going to wait
for you outside.

1965

02:18:27,006 --> 02:18:29,207
Didn't I tell you
he'd be here?

1966

02:18:29,286 --> 02:18:30,766
- Look at this crowd!
- Wow!

1967

02:18:30,847 --> 02:18:32,726
And look who's here,
our rivals.

1968

02:18:32,807 --> 02:18:33,806
What do you know?

1969

02:18:33,887 --> 02:18:36,007
Oh, you guys heard
about it, too, huh?

1970

02:18:36,047 --> 02:18:37,047
No secrets.

1971

02:18:37,127 --> 02:18:39,247
-No secrets in this country!
-well, what are you gonna do?

1972

02:18:44,247 --> 02:18:47,167
Hello, Major.
Well, what a coincidence!

1973

02:18:47,247 --> 02:18:48,808
You got a story
for us, sir?

1974

02:18:50,287 --> 02:18:52,368
No. As a matter
of fact, I don't.

1975

02:18:52,408 --> 02:18:55,168
Oh, now, Major, you're
not going to try to deny it, are you?

1976

02:18:55,248 --> 02:18:57,168
- Deny what?
- Well, the story.

1977

02:18:57,208 --> 02:18:59,888
Why won't you give us a story?
You're big news now, sir.

1978

02:18:59,969 --> 02:19:02,128
I'm afraid I don't know
what you're talking about.

1979

02:19:04,769 --> 02:19:06,369
Here's Hana-ogi.
Maybe she'll talk.

1980

02:19:23,369 --> 02:19:26,609
Come on, Hana-ogi, that's not fair.
What did you say?

1981

02:19:27,810 --> 02:19:31,490
It is very difficult
for a Japanese woman to speak in public.

1982

02:19:32,810 --> 02:19:34,530
I have never done so.

1983

02:19:35,570 --> 02:19:37,690
But perhaps now
it is the time.

1984

02:19:39,370 --> 02:19:41,810
Major Gruver has
asked me to be his...

1985

02:19:42,290 --> 02:19:43,411
His wife.

1986

02:19:47,411 --> 02:19:49,691
He knows there
are many people in his country

1987

02:19:49,770 --> 02:19:52,171
who will be
disturbed by this.

1988

02:19:52,211 --> 02:19:54,731
I know my people
will be shocked, too.

1989

02:19:55,091 --> 02:19:57,811
But I hope they will
learn to understand

1990

02:19:58,491 --> 02:20:00,211
and someday approve.

1991

02:20:01,291 --> 02:20:04,891
We are not afraid
because we know this is right.

1992

02:20:06,172 --> 02:20:08,492
I hope I can
continue as a dancer.

1993

02:20:09,371 --> 02:20:11,412
And I hope, when I am old,

1994

02:20:11,652 --> 02:20:14,332
I will be able to
teach children to dance.

1995

02:20:15,252 --> 02:20:16,532
My own children.

1996

02:20:17,972 --> 02:20:19,052
Major?

1997

02:20:19,093 --> 02:20:21,052
The big brass are
gonna yell their heads off about this.

1998

02:20:21,133 --> 02:20:23,252
And the Japanese
aren't going to like it much, either.

1999

02:20:23,333 --> 02:20:25,533
Have you got anything
to say to them, sir?

2000

02:20:27,892 --> 02:20:28,893
Yeah.

2001

02:20:30,293 --> 02:20:31,733
Tell them we said sayonara.

2002

02:20:31,973 --> 02:20:35,414
Sayonara

2003

02:20:35,573 --> 02:20:39,053
Japanese goodbye

2004

02:20:39,333 --> 02:20:42,774
Whisper sayonara

2005

02:20:42,973 --> 02:20:46,494
Lover, don't you cry

2006

02:20:46,894 --> 02:20:50,294
No more we stop to see

2007

02:20:50,534 --> 02:20:53,974
Pretty cherry blossom

2008

02:20:54,294 --> 02:20:58,055
No more we beneath the tree

2009

02:20:58,134 --> 02:21:01,415
Looking at the sky

2010

02:21:01,975 --> 02:21:05,095
Sayonara

2011

02:21:05,655 --> 02:21:09,175
Sayonara

2012

02:21:09,375 --> 02:21:13,255
Goodbye


